Fill and boil your kettle. Bring a #large saucepan{} of @water{150%ml} to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp} for the potatoes. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). When boiling, add the potatoes and cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}.

> The potatoes are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through them.

Once cooked, drain the potatoes in a #colander{}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium high heat. Add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} and stir fry until golden brown, ~{3-4%minutes}. Once the bacon is browned, remove to a #bowl{} and set aside.

Pop your pan back on medium high heat. Add the @chicken thigh{260%g}(diced) and sprinkle over the @plain flour{8%g}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Stir together to coat the chicken. Cook until golden on the outside, ~{3-5%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

While the chicken cooks, trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways then thinly slice. Trim the @green beans{80%g} then chop into thirds.

Once the chicken is browned, add the leek and @sliced mushrooms{120%g} to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and cook until the mushrooms have browned and the leek softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

Once the veggies are soft, add in the @red wine stock paste{28%g} and boiling water (see ingredient list for amount). Add the green beans and bacon, bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve stock pot. Simmer until the beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}, then remove from the heat. Taste and add @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if you feel it needs it. Add a splash of water if it's a bit thick.

Put your potatoes back in the pan and add a knob of @butter{} and a splash of @?milk{} if you have it. Grate in the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g} and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Serve in #bowls{} with the chicken stew on top. Enjoy!

> MOD Step 2: If you've decided to add bacon to your meal, before cooking the chicken, heat a drizzle of oil in a large frying pan on medium high heat. Add the bacon lardons and stir fry until golden brown, 3-4 mins. Once the bacon is browned, remove to a bowl and set aside. Follow the rest of the step accordingly (using the same frying pan to cook your chicken in).

> MOD Step 5: If you've chosen to add bacon to your meal, add the cooked bacon to the pan along with the green beans to the pan. Then follow the rest of the recipe.